When ctags with JSON support is available (goal 01), provide a manual, opt-in CMake pseudo-target named `ctags-json` that runs ctags in JSON output mode over the file list produced by the cmake/scripts/ script from goal 02 and writes the result to $BUILDDIR/generated/ctags/tags.json. It must not depend on individual headers, so normal builds never regenerate it; it refreshes only when the developer explicitly builds the `ctags-json` target. This JSON file feeds the class/struct-name extraction (goal 04) and is intentionally separate from the Vi-format editor tags file, which the build system does not manage.
